ial Worker Endorsement    Apply to the PEL Program        Apply to the PEL Program       Requirements for Application to the PEL Program       Applicant must have an MSW from a CSWE-accredited program with a grade point average of at least 3.00 on a 4.00 scale (A=4.00), and  Demonstrated evidence of commitment to work with children.   To be eligible to register for courses, prospective students must submit an application and all supplemental materials listed to the Jane Addams College of Social Work (see below).      Download the Application        Full PEL Application Packet          References Form Only           Supplemental Materials   These materials must be included with your application:   Official transcript denoting a MSW degree from a CSWE-accredited program with GPA of at least 3.00 on a 4.00 scale,  Two letters of recommendation from professionals in the field,  Resume, and  Personal statement.        Submit Your Application   For Fall 2020 enrollment, application materials are due by March 20, 2020 and should be sent to:  Jane Addams College of Social Work University of Illinois at Chicago Office of Admissions 1040 West Harrison (MC 309) Chicago, Illinois 60607  If you have additional questions please contact Krista Hinton at (312) 355-2280 or by email at khinto2@uic.edu .          Academics    Back to main content           MSW Program     Program Requirements    Plan of Study    Cost & Financial Aid    Apply to the MSW Program      Field Instruction     Field Office Faculty & Staff    Field Forms for Enrolled Students    Field Instructor Resources    Prospective Field Agencies    Field Agency Search      MSW/MPH Joint Degree Program     Financial Aid    Apply to MSW/MPH Program      PhD Program     Program Requirements    Plan of Study    Cost & Financial Aid    Apply to the PhD Program    Video Info Session    Student Experiences in the PhD Program    PhD Student Profiles    PhD Program Newsletter      Professional Educator License (PEL), School Soci